<p></p>
<p>Following the GitOps pattern, deployments to OpenShift shall be defined =
as Helm charts and applied using ArgoCD.</p>
<p>Note that ArgoCD only <em>uses</em> the templating functions of Helm cha=
rts but does not actually perform a Helm deployment.</p>
<h1 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-SetupArgoCDforyourDeployments">=
<span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"acae10c3-725b-4660-8ffd-5=
14eab0814b5">Setup ArgoCD for your Deployments</span></h1>
<p>Follow the <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/ArgoCD+Setup+and+Configuration">Argo=
CD Setup and Configuration</a> guide to get your own ArgoCD instance up and=
 running.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-EnableArgoCDSyncviaTektonPipeli=
nes">Enable ArgoCD Sync via Tekton Pipelines</h2>
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"57622d79-9122-4f34-afe=
3-a52a2356e3e2">In order to allow Tekton to trigger app syncs in ArgoCD, a =
specific user </span><em><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"=
57622d79-9122-4f34-afe3-a52a2356e3e2">tektoncontroller</span></em><span cla=
ss=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"57622d79-9122-4f34-afe3-a52a2356e3=
e2"> should be created in ArgoCD and its credentials added to your Tekton b=
uild namespace</span>.</p>
<ul>
<li>When using the <a href=3D"https://code.sbb.ch/projects/OM_PAAS/repos/he=
lm-argocd/browse" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">CLEW ArgoCD char=
t</a>, the user <em>tektoncontroller</em> is already configured.</li>
<li><p class=3D"auto-cursor-target">If you're not using this chart, you hav=
e to create the user&nbsp;<em>tektoncontroller&nbsp;</em>manually:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">oc -n a=
rgocd patch configmap argocd-cm -p '{ "data": { "accounts.tektoncontroller"=
: "apiKey" } }'</pre>
</div>
</div></li>
</ul>
<p>Afterwards, you just have to generate a token for the user:</p>
<ol>
<li>Generate an access token for this user via the ArgoCD web UI:=20
<ol>
<li>navigate to <em>Settings &gt; Accounts &gt; tektoncontroller</em></li>
<li>in the section <em>Tokens</em> click "Generate New"</li>
<li>copy the new token<code><br></code></li>
</ol></li>
<li><p>Enter the ArgoCD host name (without https://) and the generated acce=
ss token to the secret with the name <code>argocd-env-secret</code>.</p>
<ol>
<li><p>in the <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/Tekton+Control+Panel">Tekton Control=
 Panel</a>, navigate to <em>Pipeline Secrets</em></p></li>
<li><p>edit the secret <code>argocd-env-secret</code> and save the changes<=
/p></li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-ConnecttodifferentArgoCDinstanc=
esfromTektonPipelines">Connect to different ArgoCD instances from Tekton Pi=
pelines</h2>
<p>By default, Tekton pipelines use the <code>argocd-env-secret</code> to c=
onnect to ArgoCD but you can create additional secrets with the keys <code>=
ARGOCD_SERVER</code> and <code>ARGOCD_AUTH_TOKEN</code> and reference the s=
ecret name in the <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/ESTA+Tekton+Parameters+-+estaTek=
tonPipeline.json">stage config</a> of your <code>estaTektonPipeline.json</c=
ode>:</p>
<pre><span style=3D"color: rgb(135,16,148);">"stages"</span>: [<br>  {<br> =
   <span style=3D"color: rgb(135,16,148);">"stageName"</span>: <span style=
=3D"color: rgb(6,125,23);">"dev"</span>,<br>    <span style=3D"color: rgb(1=
35,16,148);">"argoCD"</span>: {<br>      <span style=3D"color: rgb(135,16,1=
48);">"argoCdAppName"</span>: <span style=3D"color: rgb(6,125,23);">"&lt;ar=
gocd-appname&gt;"</span>,<br>      <span style=3D"color: rgb(135,16,148);">=
"autoSync"</span>: <span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,179);">true</span>,<br>  =
    <span style=3D"color: rgb(135,16,148);">"argoCdSecret"</span>: <span st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(6,125,23);">"argocd-env-secret-&lt;some-name&gt;"</span>
  <span style=3D"color: rgb(6,125,23);">  </span>}<br>  }<br>],</pre>
<p>You can manage these secrets directly in the <em>Pipeline Secrets</em> s=
ection of your <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/Tekton+Control+Panel">Tekton Contro=
l Panel</a>.</p>
<h1 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-CreateHelmCharts">Create Helm C=
harts</h1>
<p>If your start from scratch, have a look at the <a href=3D"https://code.s=
bb.ch/projects/KD_ESTA_BLUEPRINTS/repos/esta-argocd/browse/applications" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker=
" data-ref=3D"5f4fa0dd-d827-484c-8b06-4dd63c7bf815">esta-argocd blueprint</=
span></a> providing a sample Helm chart with the minimal required resources=
 to get an application running on OpenShift.</p>
<p>Another way is to use the <a href=3D"https://helm.sh/docs/intro/install/=
" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Helm CLI</a> to create a new cha=
rt:</p>
<pre>$ helm create &lt;chart-name&gt;.</pre>
<p>The generated chart, however, might be too complex and includes resource=
s like HorizontalPodAutoscaler and Ingress which are not needed in our envi=
ronments.</p>
<h2 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-UmbrellaCharts">Umbrella Charts=
</h2>
<p>Helm charts have the ability to include other charts, referred to as sub=
charts, via their <a href=3D"https://helm.sh/docs/helm/helm_dependency/" cl=
ass=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">dependencies </a>section. When a cha=
rt is created for the purpose of grouping together related subcharts/servic=
es, such as to compose a whole set of micro-service deployments, we call th=
is an umbrella chart. Use this technique to orchestrate complex deployments=
 with cross-dependencies.</p>
<p>In order to use a Helm chart of an application/service as a dependency i=
n an umbrella helm chart, the former needs to packaged and published to a H=
elm chart repository. Tekton build pipelines will do that for you and can p=
ush versioned charts to Artifactory (bin.sbb.ch/artifactory/xxxx.helm). Ena=
ble the <span> <code>packageAndDeployHelmChart</code> flag in your <code>es=
taTektonPipeline.json</code> <a href=3D"https://confluence.sbb.ch/display/C=
LEW/ESTA+Tekton+Parameters+-+estaTektonPipeline.json#ESTATektonParameterses=
taTektonPipeline.json-Buildpipelineconfigurationstructure" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>build pipeline config</a> and define the repository name using the <code>c=
hartRepository</code> property in the <a href=3D"https://confluence.sbb.ch/=
display/CLEW/ESTA+Tekton+Parameters+-+estaTektonPipeline.json#ESTATektonPar=
ametersestaTektonPipeline.json-Helmconfigurationstructure" rel=3D"nofollow"=
>Helm configuration structure</a>.</span></p>
<h2 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-Bestpracticesuggestions">Best p=
ractice suggestions</h2>
<p>Besides the <a href=3D"https://helm.sh/docs/chart_best_practices/templat=
es/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Best Practices</a> suggested =
by Helm, we'd like to highlight the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create a <code>values-xxx.yaml</code> file for each stage/environment (=
e.g. dev, test, int. prod)</li>
<li>Read the deployment version of the app (=E2=86=92 docker image tags, et=
c.) from .Values to maintain them individually for each stage</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-MigrateOpenShiftTemplatestoHelm=
Charts">Migrate OpenShift Templates to Helm Charts</h2>
<p>ESTA provides a tool to help you migrate existing OpenShift templates in=
to Helm charts.<br>
 See the <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/OpenShift-Helm-Migration">OpenShift-Helm-=
Migration</a> section for details.</p>
<h1 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-ManageArgoCDDeploymentsinGit(ap=
pofapps)">Manage ArgoCD Deployments in Git (app of apps)</h1>
<p>Although new applications can easily be added to ArgoCD via the UI or as=
 Kubernetes resources (kind: Application), they're only persisted in OpenSh=
ift and may be lost during migration or due to accidental deletion. Therefo=
re we recommend the declarative approach to manage them in Git and let Argo=
CD sync its own configuration.</p>
<p>Read more about the <strong>app of apps pattern</strong> in the <a href=
=3D"https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/en/stable/operator-manual/cluster-bootst=
rapping/#app-of-apps-pattern" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Argo=
CD docs</a> or use fork the <a href=3D"https://code.sbb.ch/projects/KD_ESTA=
_BLUEPRINTS/repos/esta-argocd/browse" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofoll=
ow">ESTA ArgoCD Blueprint</a>.</p>
<h1 id=3D"DeploymentwithArgoCDandHelmCharts-UpdateArgoCDValuesfromTektonPip=
elines">Update ArgoCD Values from Tekton Pipelines</h1>
<p>See the Staging Section of <a href=3D"/display/CLEW/ESTA+Tekton+Paramete=
rs+-+estaTektonPipeline.json">ESTA Tekton Parameters</a> to learn how to up=
date deployment versions in ArgoCD after successful builds in ESTA Tekton.<=
/p>
